### Base URL
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3000/api

---
### AUTHENTICATION ENDPOINTS
---

# REGISTRATION FLOW
# /register  : sends OTP, returns signup token
# /verify-otp: submits OTP + token, creates account
# /resend-otp : resend a fresh OTP if it expired


### 1. Register (Initiate signup — sends OTP to email)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/register
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "",
  "password": "",
  "full_name": "",
  "phone": "",
  "user_type": ""
}

###

### 2. Verify OTP (Complete registration)
# Use the token returned by /register above
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/verify-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "<paste_signup_token_here>",
  "otp": ""
}

###

### 3. Resend OTP (Use the old/expired token — a new one is returned)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/resend-otp
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "<paste_signup_token_here>"
}

###


### Login User
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "",
  "password": ""
}

###


### Get Current User (Protected — requires Bearer token)
@authToken = <paste_auth_token_here>

GET {{baseUrl}}/auth/me
Authorization: Bearer {{authToken}}

# PASSWORD RESET FLOW
# /forgot-password : sends reset OTP, returns reset token
#  /reset-password  : submits OTP + token + new password

### Forgot Password (Request reset OTP)
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/forgot-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "customer@example.com"
}


### Reset Password (Set new password using OTP)
# Use the token returned by /forgot-password above
POST {{baseUrl}}/auth/reset-password
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "token": "<paste_reset_token_here>",
  "otp": "123456",
  "newPassword": "newSecurePassword123"
}

